---  
description: Use when debugging Sitecore XM Cloud component setup problems such as empty datasource pickers, missing insert options, bad GraphQL queries, props mismatches, or variant issues.  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Troubleshooting map:  
  
1. Datasource picker is empty  
- Check content folder exists under `/Data`  
- Check folder template exists under `/Folders`  
- Check folder template `__Standard Values` has `__Masters`  
- Check `Datasource Location` query matches folder template name exactly  
- Check datasource items exist inside the folder  
  
2. "No datasource template found"  
- Check rendering `Datasource Template`  
- Must be a full template path, not a GUID  
- Ensure the template exists  
  
3. Children missing in component  
- Check rendering has `ComponentQuery`  
- Check query includes `children { results { ... } }`  
- Check React reads from `fields.data.datasource.children.results`  
  
4. Props shape mismatch  
- If no query: use top-level `fields.Title`, `fields.Description`  
- If query exists: use `fields.data.datasource`  
- If context-only: use `page.layout.sitecore.route.fields`  
  
5. "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'route')"  
- Suspect malformed `ComponentQuery`  
- Validate syntax, fragment names, field names, and collisions  
  
6. Add button in Pages Content tab shows no templates  
- Check parent template `__Standard Values`  
- Set `__Masters` to child template IDs  
- Ensure parent template inherits `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping`  
  
7. Variant dropdown missing or variant not switching  
- Check Headless Variant Definition items exist  
- Check names exactly match code exports  
- Ensure `Default` exists  